## 6. MEMBERSHIPS — SYSTEM MODEL

Fourthwall Memberships combines homepage, shop, exclusive content hub, messaging, perks, and supporter management in one branded experience.

Dashboard areas: Overview · Posts · Messages · Video Series · Members · Perks & Tiers · Settings

### 6.1 Core Components

**Tiers** — pricing levels supporters join. Need at least one to launch. Each defines: price, billing cadence, perks, trial/intro options, free or paid.

**Perks** — actual reasons someone joins. Types: Custom perk · Discord · Members-only discounts · Members-only products · Private audio RSS feed.

**Content** — posts that drive conversion and retention. Types: text, image, video, audio, polls, welcome posts, DMs, locked messages.

**Member states** — Fourthwall has a full lifecycle, not just "paid members":
```
Free account · Free tier member · Paid active member · Free trial member
Expiring member · Former member
```

### 6.2 Tier Strategy

**Single-tier model** — best for simplicity, clear value prop, merch/community-first offers, low complexity. Strong use cases: merch club, Discord + discount club, "support the work."

**Multi-tier model** — best for price segmentation and escalating access:
```
Entry tier   → support + basic perks
Middle tier  → more access / content
Top tier     → exclusivity, recognition, deeper connection
```

**Free tier** — set price to $0. All free accounts auto-assigned. Currently only supports custom perks, not Discord or advanced paid-tier perks.

**Annual subscriptions** — enable under Memberships → Settings → General. Improves cash flow, retention, and reduces monthly churn. Fourthwall auto-calculates yearly total.

**Intro pricing** — one-time launch discount at tier level. Applies to first billing period only.

### 6.3 Perk Reference

**Custom perks** — most flexible. Good for promises, entitlements, branded experiences: early access, AMAs, shoutouts, request privileges, VIP recognition, surprise drops.

**Discord perk** — highest-value community perk. Connects Memberships → Discord roles.
```
Setup flow:
1. Create roles in Discord
2. Connect Discord in Fourthwall
3. Assign Discord perk to tiers
4. Fourthwall bot joins server
5. Members authenticate at /supporters/perks
6. Bot assigns correct role automatically

CRITICAL: Fourthwall bot must retain permission to manage assigned roles, or setup breaks.
```

**Members-only discounts** — two-layer setup:
1. Add "members-only discount" perk to tiers
2. Create shop promo in Promotions with requirement = **Members only**, define eligible tiers, discount amount, product scope

**Members-only products** — lock specific products to members:
1. Add perk to tiers
2. Edit product → enable members-only → choose tiers
Products show "Members-only" badges publicly, which helps sell the membership.

**Private audio RSS feed** — personal RSS link per member, paste into Apple Podcasts or any podcast app. Configure: feed title, image, included tags, eligible tiers. Requires at least one audio post.

### 6.4 Content System

**Welcome posts** — appear at top of member feed for 24h, always accessible from Perks tab. Options: no post, same post for all tiers, or per-tier posts. Formats: text, image, video.

**Posts** — created in Memberships → Posts. Visibility: everyone / all members / selected tiers / free members.

**Public posts** — serve three functions: engage free accounts, keep former members warm, bridge free-to-paid conversion.

### 6.5 Direct Messages and Locked Messages

**DMs** — one-to-one communication between creator and members. Target: all members, selected tiers, expiring members, former members, free accounts. Sends as individual messages (not group chat). Enable under Memberships → Settings → Messages.

**Tips in messages** — supporters can attach tips. Configure: enabled, disabled, or minimum tip ($1–$100). Minimum tips reduce spam and make inbox access feel premium.

**Locked messages (PPV)** — pay-per-view DMs. Content: text, images, one video, one audio. Price: $1–$100. Former/expired members can unlock but cannot reply unless they rejoin. Audio/video processing can take up to 1 hour. Edit/delete after sending is not supported. Track revenue: Analytics → Full report → filter by **Memberships paid message**.

### 6.6 Free Accounts

Free accounts are a built-in audience layer — not paying, but in your system. Sources: explicit signup, former paid members, abandoned checkouts where account was created.

Free accounts can: receive public post notifications, view/like/comment on public posts, see members-only content in locked state, upgrade later.

Free accounts cannot: access members-only posts, receive paid-tier perks.

You can hide free account promotion in settings, but free accounts continue to exist in the system regardless.

### 6.7 Discounts and Promos

**7-day free trial** — first-time members only. Former members cannot reuse (unless different email). Trial ends if upgrading during trial.

**Introductory one-time discount** — automatic, no code required, applies to first billing period only.

**Promo codes** — create under Promotions → Create promotion → Membership promo. Configure: single or multi-code, discount %, monthly/annual/all, all or selected tiers, new members only. No usage caps yet.

**Twitch subscriber discounts** — verify active Twitch sub → apply discounted pricing. Max discount: 80%. Persists only while Twitch sub remains active. Reverts if sub lapses.

**Key limitation:** discounts only apply to one billing period. Multi-month/multi-year durations not supported.

### 6.8 Member Management

Cancel a subscription: Memberships → Members → open member → Cancel subscription. Choose timing (immediate or end of cycle) and refund behavior (full, prorated, custom, none). Only the latest payment is refundable during cancellation — refund earlier payments separately afterward. Cancellation is irreversible; member must resubscribe.

Refunding without canceling: refund past transactions without ending the subscription. Refund types: full, prorated, custom. Irreversible. Refunding a payment does not stop renewal.

### 6.9 Membership: Three-Layer Strategic Model

```
Layer A — Acquisition
  Tools: free accounts, free tier, public posts, homepage tier visibility,
         launch promos, promo codes, Twitch discounts, members-only product teasers

Layer B — Retention
  Tools: welcome posts, exclusive posts, discounts, exclusive merch,
         Discord roles, DMs, custom badges, annual plans

Layer C — Expansion
  Tools: higher tiers, locked messages / PPV, upsells from lower tiers,
         annual billing, Twitch discounts, exclusive drops, custom perks
```

### 6.10 Membership Badges

**Streak badge** — default, duration-based. "New member" (month 1) → "X-month member" thereafter. Customize global style or per-streak-length styling.

**Custom badges** — define eligibility by: tier membership, comments written, likes given, likes received, or manual assignment. Customize text, icon, border/bg/text colors. Custom icon upload not yet supported.

Badge display: only one badge shows by default beside nickname; others tuck behind `+X`. Supporters can reorder their own badges. Streak badge can be disabled but not deleted.

### 6.11 Mobile App

When Memberships is enabled, a mobile web app is automatically available (PWA — not App Store / Google Play).

Benefits: branded, push notifications, no Apple/Google 30% cut, audio background playback, AirPlay/Chromecast support.

Limitations: no background video playback, no picture-in-picture, no offline video, not listed in app stores, tablets not supported.

Install flow: iOS → Share → Add to Home Screen. Android → automated install prompt.

Push notifications: Android + iOS 16.4+.

### 6.12 Memberships: Known Limitations

- Custom badge icon upload not yet supported
- Edit/delete for sent DMs and locked messages not supported
- Multiple-month/multi-year membership discounts not supported
- Promo usage caps not yet available
- Detailed locked-message unlock analytics not yet available
- General push notifications for broad announcements not yet in mobile app
- Free tiers support custom perks only — no Discord or advanced perk types
- Mobile app cannot be disabled by creator in self-serve settings
- App icon/title changes require reinstall for existing users
- Tablets not supported in mobile app

