## 8. STOREFRONT DEPLOYMENT OPTIONS

```
OPTION 1   Fourthwall-hosted (default)
           Fast setup. Limited customization.

OPTION 2   Proxy architecture (recommended for custom storefronts)
           Customer → Next.js frontend → Backend proxy → Storefront API
           Keeps token server-side. Full design control.

OPTION 3   Static frontend
           Customer → Frontend → Storefront API directly
           Token visible client-side — acceptable for read-only public data.

OFFICIAL   Fork https://github.com/FourthwallHQ/vercel-commerce
           Set storefront_token env var → deploy to Vercel
```

Minimal custom storefront flow:
```
1. POST /v1/carts                          → get cart_id
2. POST /v1/carts/{cart_id}/items          → add variantId
3. GET  /v1/carts/{cart_id}                → review cart
4. Redirect → /checkout/?cartCurrency=USD&cartId={cart_id}
```

