## 10. MERCH & PRODUCT SPECS `⚠️ C15`

### 10.1 Universal Upload Requirements

```
Format         PNG preferred · JPEG accepted · No TIFF
               PNG required for any product needing transparency
Resolution     300 DPI recommended · 200 DPI floor for DTG garments
Upload size    ~25 MB max per file
Transparency   Full alpha only — no glows, semi-transparent edges, or fade effects
Bleed          Extend background past safe-area dotted line in editor
               Keep text/faces/logos well inside safe zone
Quality UI     Blue = pass · Yellow = fair · Red = too low
Color          Work in RGB, export CMYK only for print. Exception: poster/inkjet = stay sRGB
Sublimation    Colors print darker/less saturated — push brightness and saturation 10–15%
```

### 10.2 Master Canvas Strategy

Create one master file large enough to cover every product. Derive all exports from it.

```
Minimum:   13,500px on long edge at 300 PPI
Ideal:     15,000 × 9,000px at 300 PPI (landscape)
Format:    PSD or TIFF, layered, RGB
Profile:   sRGB IEC61966-2.1 or Display P3
```

Covers all Fourthwall products at 300 DPI except the 24×36 poster (treat as separate deliverable).

Three derived crops from one master:
```
Landscape  ~15,000 × 9,000px  (desk mats, banners, gaming pads)
Square     ~9,000 × 9,000px   (10×10 prints, coasters, profile pics)
Portrait   ~7,200 × 10,800px  (18×24 posters — requires composition planning)
```

### 10.3 Product Pixel Dimensions

**Desk Mats** (Sublimation / Spoke):

| Size | Print Area | Pixels @ 300 DPI |
|---|---|---|
| Small | 12 × 18″ | 3,600 × 5,400 |
| Medium | 12 × 22″ | 3,600 × 6,600 |
| Large | 15.5 × 31.5″ | 4,650 × 9,450 |

**Mouse Pads** (Sublimation / Printful):

| Size | Print Area | Pixels @ 300 DPI |
|---|---|---|
| Classic | 8.7 × 7.1″ | 2,610 × 2,130 |
| Gaming Medium | 18 × 16″ | 5,400 × 4,800 |
| Gaming Large | 36 × 18″ | 10,800 × 5,400 |

**Coasters, Posters, Prints** (Printful):

| Product | Print Area | Pixels @ 300 DPI |
|---|---|---|
| Coaster | 3.74 × 3.74″ | 1,122 × 1,122 |
| Poster 10×10 | 10 × 10″ | 3,000 × 3,000 |
| Poster 18×24 | 18 × 24″ | 5,400 × 7,200 |
| Poster 24×36 | 24 × 36″ | 7,200 × 10,800 |

### 10.4 Print Methods Summary

| Method | Products | Color note |
|---|---|---|
| Sublimation | Desk mats, mouse pads, coasters | Darker/less saturated than screen — compensate +10–15% |
| Digital inkjet / giclée | Posters, art prints | Most accurate — stay in sRGB |
| DTG | T-shirts, lightweight apparel | Min 200 DPI · PNG transparent bg |
| DTFx | Hoodies, heavyweight apparel | Brighter than DTG · avoid large solid fills on lightweight |
| Screen printing | MOQ products only | No gradients — solid shapes only |
| Embroidery | Branded accessories | Max 5–6 thread colors · min line 0.05″ · no gradients |

### 10.5 DPI by Viewing Distance

| Product | Typical distance | Required DPI | Practical min pixels |
|---|---|---|---|
| Coaster | 12–18″ (hand) | 250–300 | 1,122 × 1,122 |
| Classic mouse pad | 18–24″ (desk) | 200–300 | 2,610 × 2,130 |
| Gaming mouse pad | 18–24″ (desk) | 200–300 | 5,400 × 4,800 |
| Desk mat | 24–30″ (arm) | 150–250 | 3,100 × 6,300 (200 DPI) |
| 10×10 poster | 2–3 ft (wall) | 150–200 | 2,000 × 2,000 |
| 18×24 poster | 3–5 ft (wall) | 100–150 | 3,600 × 4,800 (200 DPI) |
| 24×36 poster | 4–6 ft (wall) | 75–120 | 4,800 × 7,200 (200 DPI) |

Always upload highest resolution available — Fourthwall handles downsampling.

### 10.6 Digital Platform Asset Dimensions

**YouTube:**

| Asset | Dimensions | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Banner (upload) | 2560 × 1440px | Full canvas for TV display |
| Banner safe zone | 1546 × 423px | Centered. All critical content here. |
| Profile picture | 800 × 800px | Displayed as circle |
| Thumbnail | 1280 × 720px | Max 2 MB |

**Twitch / Discord:**

| Platform | Asset | Dimensions |
|---|---|---|
| Twitch | Banner | 1200 × 480px (1920 × 480 retina) |
| Twitch | Profile picture | 800 × 800px (circle) |
| Twitch | Offline screen | 1920 × 1080px |
| Discord | Server banner | 960 × 540px |
| Discord | Server icon | 512 × 512px (circle) |

**OBS Overlays:**
```
Canvas size    1920 × 1080px (match OBS Base Canvas Resolution exactly)
Format         PNG-32 (RGBA) — PNG-8 unsupported for anti-aliased elements
Color profile  sRGB IEC61966-2.1 — OBS does no color management/ICC conversion
Performance    Static PNG overlays have negligible GPU impact once loaded
               Separate elements into individual PNGs for Stream Deck toggling
```

### 10.7 File Naming Convention

`[ArtworkTitle]_[ProductType]_[Dimensions]_[ColorMode]_v[##].png`

Examples:
```
MoonlitForest_DeskMat_15x31_CMYK_v01.png
MoonlitForest_Poster_10x10_sRGB_v01.png
MoonlitForest_YTBanner_2560x1440_sRGB_v01.png
MoonlitForest_Master_15000x9000_RGB.psd
```

Rules: underscores not spaces · leading zeros on versions · ISO dates if needed (YYYYMMDD) · under 50 chars where possible · never edit exports — return to master and re-export.

### 10.8 Delivery Folder Structure

```
ProjectName/
├── Source/          (master PSD/TIFF, all layers, RGB)
├── Print/           (flattened, CMYK where needed, per product)
├── Digital/         (sRGB, web-optimized, social crops)
├── Overlays/        (1920×1080 PNG-32, sRGB, transparent)
└── Reference/       (mockups, crop guides, notes)
```

